    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Still Wise to Have a Mammogram</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Diane Palacios letter on March 1 article scores her doctors for denying there may be risk associated with mammogram</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Senators Hear From Experts, Then Support Mammography'' (news article, March 1):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Senators Hear From Experts, Then Support Mammography'' (news article, March 1):</p>
        <p>I am a 58-year-old woman who has always been concerned about living a healthy lifestyle. I have not chosen to get a mammogram every year because I have read that there are risks associated with that procedure.</p>
        <p>I do not find it troubling to hear Dr. Donald Berry testify that the benefits of mammograms do not outweigh the risks.</p>
        <p>What I have always found troubling is the refusal of my doctors over the last 18 years to explain to me that there are any risks at all associated with mammograms.</p>
        <p>I can live with uncertainty. I do not wish to live with dishonesty.</p>
        <p>DIANE PALACIOS  Ridgewood, N.J., March 1, 2002</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
